Intensity       -    Light intensity
Intensity       +    Heavy intensity
Descriptor      VC   In the vicinity (5–10 mi / 8–16 km from station)
Descriptor      RE   Recent hour's most important past phenomenon with residues
Descriptor      MI   Fog descriptor: Shallow [French: Mince]
Descriptor      PR   Fog descriptor: Partial
Descriptor      BC   Fog descriptor: Patches [French: Bancs]
Descriptor      DR   Low drifting below eye level
Descriptor      BL   Blowing at or above eye level
Descriptor*     SH   Showers
Descriptor*     TS   Thunderstorm
Descriptor      FZ   Freezing
Precipitation   DZ   Drizzle
Precipitation   RA   Rain
Precipitation   SN   Snow (snowflakes)
Precipitation   SG   Snow grains
Precipitation   GS   Graupel [French: Grésil] (hail < 5mm, not in the US)
Precipitation   GR   Hail [French: Grêle] (hail >= 5mm, any hail in the US)
Precipitation   PL   Ice pellets
Precipitation   IC   Ice crystals
Precipitation   UP   Unknown precipitation
Obscuration     FG   Fog (visibility less than 1 km)
Obscuration     BR   Mist [French: Brume] (water droplets, visibility between 1 and 5 km)
Obscuration     HZ   Haze (dry particulates, visibility between 1 and 5 km)
Obscuration     VA   Volcanic ash
Obscuration     DU   Widespread dust
Obscuration     FU   Smoke [French: Fumée]
Obscuration     SA   Sand
Obscuration     PY   Spray, only coded as BLPY
Other           SQ   Squall
Other           PO   Dust [French: Poussière] or sand whirls
Other           DS   Duststorm
Other           SS   Sandstorm
Other           FC   Funnel cloud
